occupation: Graduate Teaching Assistant & Student Assistant at Illinois Institute of Technology
headline: Actively seeking full time opportunities | Master's in IT & Management | Salesforce Certified | Expert in Java, Python, SQL | Transforming Data into Insights | DevOps Enthusiast | Graduate Teaching Assistant
summary:
As a graduate teaching assistant and student assistant at Illinois Institute of Technology, I am pursuing my master's degree in Information Technology and Management. I have a strong academic background in Java development, as well as multiple certifications in Salesforce and Oracle, two of the leading cloud-based platforms in the IT industry.

I have also gained valuable professional experience as an associate software engineer at Accenture, where I orchestrated deployment and delivery in Salesforce CRM using Flosum, ensuring alignment with project and user requirements. I collaborated with senior DevOps engineers to develop and apply innovative branching and environment techniques, enhancing code quality to exceed 90%. I also executed SQL queries using Workbench, retrieving essential data from CRM for analysis and decision-making. I am flexible, adaptable, and eager to learn and work in a dynamic IT environment, with a passion for transforming data into insights.

accomplishment_projects.title: Chicago Crime Data
accomplishment_projects.description:
Data Analysis Project Completion: Accomplished a comprehensive data analysis and visualization initiative utilizing Python, with a specific focus on crime data originating from the city of Chicago.
End-to-End Data Handling: Applied adept data collection techniques, proficient data processing methods, and cutting-edge data visualization tools to distill insightful patterns and trends from an extensive dataset of crime records in Chicago. Interactive GUI Implementation: Designed and implemented an engaging graphical user interface (GUI) to empower users in exploring and visualizing crime trends across various neighborhoods in Chicago. 
Diverse Visualization Techniques: Employed a variety of visualization methods, including bar charts, pie charts, and line graphs, to effectively convey critical insights derived from the crime data. Communication of Key Findings: Successfully communicated key findings and patterns within the crime data through visually compelling and accessible graphical representations. 
Holistic Project Contribution: Played a pivotal role in all aspects of the project, from data extraction and processing to the development of an interactive GUI, showcasing proficiency in data analytics and visualization.

Diverse Functionalities: Encompassed a range of functionalities, including schema design, performance optimization, database connectivity, and data analytics.
